content.description:
Start on the right side of the block climb up to the low angle face.  Continue to the top on thin holds and foot smears.               

Kasey on the Right End.
content.location: On the right side of the block.

content.description:
Climb the crack on the right side of the face.               

Divya climbing the right crack.
content.location: The right side of the block.  See the picture.

content.description:
Climb the crack in the center of the block.  The crack is more like a Flake that requires layback moves.  I was informed this is known as a V0 highball problem.  Didn't catch the historical name.              

Kasey on The Left Crack
content.protection: Good crack. Short lead? Sure, why not.Top rope from trees.A thick crash pad or two?
content.location: Start below the crack in the center of the block.

content.description:
Climb up the overhanging face to the horizontal crack. Stand up on it using holds on the left edge.  Then move up and right until the bolt is chest high.  Pull thru the thin crux here to the top.               

Kasey on the crux of the Bolt Route.
content.protection: Trees for top system.It has a crack and a bolt. A very sporty lead?
content.location: Start on the left end of the block.

content.description:
Moe's Cut is suitable for bouldering or top rope. It's SE exposure would make for nice cool weather climbing. Solid clean rock.  It's worth at least 1 visit if you climb near in frederick watershed.               

Kasey on The Left Crack
